The paper deals with algorithmic problems related to graphs, such as pricing and approximation algorithms, and studies them on special classes of graphs such as those with bounded treewidth, bounded genus, and $k$-partite graphs. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
